[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stamp of approval for Dylan Thomas on Swansea postbox

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A plaque of Dylan Thomas has been unveiled on a postbox as part of the celebration marking 50 years of Royal Mail special stamps.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Welsh poet's granddaughter Hannah Ellis revealed the plaque showing his stamp on a postbox in King's Road, Swansea, near the Dylan Thomas Centre.
The stamp was issued in 2014 as part of the Remarkable Lives issue.
A plaque of the Tenby lifeboat stamp, issued in 2008, was also unveiled at a postbox in Tudor Square in the town.
